WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.270
<i>Previously
on "Fantasy Island"...</i>

00:03.270 --> 00:05.672
I think this old chair
was your great-uncle's,

00:05.672 --> 00:09.109
- but I redid the rattan and--
- This is perfect.

00:09.109 --> 00:12.012
- What's all this?
- I'm taking you to prom.

00:12.012 --> 00:14.414
<i>I have never seen
Elenita happier.</i>

00:14.414 --> 00:17.150
<i>- And I love him.
- I love you, too.</i>

00:17.150 --> 00:20.287
My fantasy is to find
my biological father.

00:20.287 --> 00:23.056
I was conceived in the middle
of a hurricane...

00:23.056 --> 00:24.424
Hurricane Helene.

00:24.525 --> 00:26.793
I was in the jungle
during Hurricane Helene.

00:26.793 --> 00:28.595
This way! I found shelter!

00:28.595 --> 00:31.632
<i>This is gonna sound crazy,
but I think I'm your daughter.</i>

00:31.632 --> 00:33.767
I don't think anyone knows
how to be a parent.

00:33.767 --> 00:36.303
Yeah, but most people get
a starter model to warm up on.

00:36.303 --> 00:38.472
She's still trying to
figure it all out.

00:38.472 --> 00:40.941
<i>Bless her.
She's mourning her mother.</i>

00:40.941 --> 00:42.242
Thanks, Dad.

00:42.242 --> 00:44.678
My birthday is me and my mom.

00:44.678 --> 00:48.949
And every time I look across
the table, she's not there.

00:49.049 --> 00:50.350
You're there.

00:50.350 --> 00:52.252
There is nothing
more important to me

00:52.252 --> 00:54.054
than your relationship
with Helene.

00:54.054 --> 00:55.255
I can't see you anymore.

00:55.255 --> 00:57.057
Please believe me
when I tell you

00:57.057 --> 00:58.192
that this is
for the best, Javier.

00:58.192 --> 00:59.660
- Elena--
- I'm sorry.

00:59.660 --> 01:02.663
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:02.663 --> 01:09.670
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:22.783 --> 01:23.717
You're good.

01:23.717 --> 01:26.787
Breaking up with Javier
was the right decision.

01:26.787 --> 01:29.122
You did the right thing.

01:29.122 --> 01:32.759
[softly]

01:32.759 --> 01:34.828
I did the right thing.

01:34.828 --> 01:36.797
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:36.797 --> 01:38.265
[inhales deeply]

01:38.265 --> 01:40.968
[normal voice]
Welcome to Fantasy Island.

01:40.968 --> 01:48.242
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:53.947 --> 01:55.115
[sighs]

01:55.115 --> 01:56.950
[in Spanish]
Good morning, Elena.

01:56.950 --> 01:58.051
- [in English]
- Good morning.

01:58.051 --> 01:59.553
Can you speak to me
in Spanish?

01:59.553 --> 02:02.089
I can't go two lifetimes
only speaking English.

02:02.189 --> 02:03.657
[in Spanish]
Good morning, Ruby.

02:03.657 --> 02:05.392
Ah.

02:05.392 --> 02:08.629
<i>[magical music]</i>

02:08.629 --> 02:09.930
Are you okay?

02:09.930 --> 02:12.366
Yes. Everything's fine.

02:12.366 --> 02:14.468
- [in English]
- Look at this place.

02:14.468 --> 02:16.236
Graham family,
I'm Elena Roarke.

02:16.236 --> 02:19.106
I'm your host,
and this is my associate, Ruby.

02:19.106 --> 02:20.641
I'm Amber.
This is my husband, Dan,

02:20.641 --> 02:23.744
and our beautiful offspring,
Ryleigh and Trevor.

02:23.744 --> 02:25.345
- [in Spanish]
- Ah, nice to meet you.

02:25.345 --> 02:28.515
<i>[somber music]</i>

02:28.515 --> 02:31.218
[in English]
Uh, please follow me this way.

02:31.218 --> 02:32.553
Oh, we aren't going anywhere

02:32.553 --> 02:34.421
until we get
our first vacation picture.

02:34.421 --> 02:36.957
Mom, seriously?
I look like a bridge troll.

02:36.957 --> 02:39.092
Ryleigh,
you're 16 and gorgeous.

02:39.092 --> 02:40.427
How about this?

02:40.427 --> 02:42.062
Ash will take you to your suite
to get settled,

02:42.062 --> 02:43.430
and I promise we'll get

02:43.430 --> 02:46.033
the perfect family photo
but a little later. [chuckles]

02:46.133 --> 02:48.802
High sun
equals harsh shadows.

02:48.802 --> 02:51.271
Okay, I'm holding you to it.

02:51.271 --> 02:53.740
I bought us the cutest
matching outfits.

02:53.740 --> 02:55.709
I am not wearing khakis.

02:55.709 --> 02:57.978
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:57.978 --> 03:00.981
- Ms. Roarke.
- Isaiah Hughes.

03:00.981 --> 03:02.216
So nice to meet in person,

03:02.216 --> 03:04.084
and you can call me Elena, please.

03:04.084 --> 03:06.553
- This is Ruby.
- Welcome, Isaiah.

03:06.653 --> 03:09.523
Mr. Hughes, this is for you.

03:10.891 --> 03:12.359
This is it?

03:12.359 --> 03:15.362
And please open it
whenever you're ready.

03:17.130 --> 03:18.599
This place has a bar, yeah?

03:18.599 --> 03:21.535
Yeah, there's a nice spot
just down the beach.

03:21.535 --> 03:23.570
Welcome to Fantasy Island.

03:23.570 --> 03:25.939
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:25.939 --> 03:28.041
What was that all about?

03:28.041 --> 03:29.243
Mr. Hughes's fantasy

03:29.243 --> 03:31.111
is to know the date
of his death,

03:31.111 --> 03:33.247
which is written
in that envelope.

03:33.247 --> 03:36.917
- [in Spanish]
- Hmm. Oh, my God.

03:36.917 --> 03:38.585
- [in English]
- Hey.

03:38.585 --> 03:40.254
Morning.

03:40.254 --> 03:41.355
Whoa.

03:41.355 --> 03:43.824
Um, a cold front just blew in.

03:43.824 --> 03:46.226
I don't know what you mean.

03:46.226 --> 03:49.129
Elena, you know
you can talk to me, right?

03:49.129 --> 03:50.731
Yes, I know.
[in Spanish] Yes, of course.

03:50.731 --> 03:53.100
[in English] Do me a favor--
um, follow up with Mr. Hughes.

03:53.100 --> 03:55.302
I can handle the Graham family.

03:55.302 --> 04:01.408
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:01.408 --> 04:04.378
<i>[dreamy music]</i>

04:04.378 --> 04:11.518
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:16.323 --> 04:18.859
My family doesn't know
I'm here for a fantasy,

04:18.859 --> 04:20.194
not even Dan.

04:20.194 --> 04:21.995
You won't say anything.
Will you?

04:21.995 --> 04:23.397
My lips are sealed.

04:23.397 --> 04:27.000
Now, tell me--
what can the Island do for you?

04:27.000 --> 04:28.869
I love my family so much,

04:28.869 --> 04:30.504
but I feel like
I'm failing them.

04:30.504 --> 04:33.040
- In what way?
- They're not happy.

04:33.040 --> 04:35.008
Nobody's happy all the time.

04:35.008 --> 04:36.844
But shouldn't we try to be?

04:36.844 --> 04:39.112
I grew up in chaos.

04:39.213 --> 04:40.747
My parents screamed
at each other constantly,

04:40.747 --> 04:43.917
breaking up and getting back
together every other week.

04:43.917 --> 04:46.186
Neither of them
could hold a job.

04:46.186 --> 04:48.255
We got evicted
from every place we lived.

04:48.255 --> 04:49.790
That must have been
very hard.

04:49.790 --> 04:52.326
I learned to cope,
and when things got really bad,

04:52.326 --> 04:55.128
I'd recite the multiplication
table to myself.

04:55.128 --> 04:57.497
If you want to know 12 times 7,
I'm your girl.

04:57.497 --> 05:00.467
Oh, and I also always know
where the exit is.

05:00.467 --> 05:02.302
Well, you've clearly
broken that cycle.

05:02.302 --> 05:04.204
I gave them everything.
I didn't have--

05:04.204 --> 05:07.074
safety, stability, encouragement.

05:07.074 --> 05:09.243
And it's not enough?

05:12.112 --> 05:13.380
Look at her.

05:13.380 --> 05:15.115
She's the star
of the tennis team.

05:15.115 --> 05:17.251
But it means nothing to her.
She wants to quit.

05:17.251 --> 05:20.254
And Trevor,
he is so damn smart,

05:20.254 --> 05:22.089
but he's living his life
on devices.

05:22.089 --> 05:24.024
Ah, he was mad at me
for posting this,

05:24.124 --> 05:26.894
but I look at it all the time.

05:26.894 --> 05:29.296
I miss him.

05:29.296 --> 05:32.432
Where does your husband, Dan,
fit into this?

05:32.432 --> 05:36.670
Nobody's bleeding and
nothing's on fire, Dan's good.

05:36.670 --> 05:39.206
We look so
in love here, don't we?

05:39.206 --> 05:41.942
Yes.
[chuckles]

05:41.942 --> 05:44.845
He doesn't even see me anymore...

05:44.845 --> 05:46.380
not like this.

05:46.480 --> 05:50.817
These pictures
are just moments.

05:50.817 --> 05:53.120
My fantasy is for my family

05:53.120 --> 05:57.991
to be as happy
as they look on social media.

05:57.991 --> 06:00.727
Can you do that?

06:00.727 --> 06:02.563
I can.

06:04.364 --> 06:07.401
Now let's go take
that family photo, come on.

06:10.337 --> 06:12.472
Hey, Roarke, what kind
of socks do pirates wear?

06:12.472 --> 06:16.243
- Oh, my God, Dad.
- Ryleigh, stand up straight.

06:16.243 --> 06:18.612
- I have no idea.
- Arrr-gyle.

06:18.612 --> 06:20.314
- Dad, it's not funny.
- Trevor, your phone.

06:20.314 --> 06:22.216
- Every time.
- Come on, buys, the faster

06:22.216 --> 06:24.151
we pull it together,
the faster this will be over.

06:24.151 --> 06:25.586
Dan, are you tucking
in your shirt?

06:25.586 --> 06:27.955
Mom, I almost
beat this level. Just let me--

06:27.955 --> 06:30.924
Stand still and look happy,
damn it.

06:30.924 --> 06:32.226
Okay.

06:32.226 --> 06:34.995
Smiles everyone.
[camera shutter clicks]

06:34.995 --> 06:36.964
Perfect.
[chuckles]

06:37.764 --> 06:42.069
Oh, get this thing off of me
before I turn basic forever.

06:42.069 --> 06:44.838
- Too late.
- [scoffs]

06:44.838 --> 06:46.139
So what do you think?

06:46.139 --> 06:49.276
We could take a day cruise,
a balloon tour.

06:49.276 --> 06:51.345
Oh, look, snorkeling.
That sounds like fun, right?

06:51.345 --> 06:54.381
[sighs] Maybe you girls
can explore the resort.

06:54.381 --> 06:55.315
See that pool?

06:55.315 --> 06:56.917
What about you and Trevor?

06:56.917 --> 06:58.852
I'm not gonna be able
to relax

06:58.852 --> 07:00.220
until I grade these papers,

07:00.220 --> 07:03.223
and he's clearly grown roots.

07:03.223 --> 07:04.591
Honey, I was hoping

07:04.591 --> 07:07.694
we could do something
together as a family.

07:07.694 --> 07:09.496
We have all weekend.

07:11.598 --> 07:12.666
[door opens]

07:12.666 --> 07:14.768
Oh, you know, Ry,
I saw some tennis courts.

07:14.768 --> 07:18.071
Maybe we could check 'em out
and get in a volley or two.

07:18.071 --> 07:21.808
Yeah,
that is so not gonna happen.

07:21.808 --> 07:23.377
[door opens, closes]

07:23.377 --> 07:27.281
Or I could just
sit here alone.

07:31.852 --> 07:33.520
Oh, wow.

07:36.256 --> 07:38.225
This is, like,
Christmas card worthy.

07:38.225 --> 07:41.028
It doesn't even need a filter.

07:41.028 --> 07:43.397
<i>[mystical whoosh]</i>

07:43.397 --> 07:46.366
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

07:46.366 --> 07:48.969
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:48.969 --> 07:52.139
You know,
on second thought...

07:52.139 --> 07:54.474
maybe we should go snorkeling.

07:54.474 --> 07:57.778
Hold up.
Did somebody say snorkeling?

07:57.778 --> 07:59.947
Because I love snorkeling.

07:59.947 --> 08:01.548
Very funny.

08:01.548 --> 08:04.017
Snorkeling's lame.
Whatever, I get it.

08:04.117 --> 08:06.086
Next boat leaves
in half an hour.

08:06.086 --> 08:07.254
Hey, Mom, you brought

08:07.254 --> 08:09.022
that reef-safe
suntan lotion, right?

08:09.022 --> 08:11.525
'Cause I am so psyched
to go snorkeling.

08:12.826 --> 08:15.696
You okay, Mom?

08:15.696 --> 08:17.698
I just...

08:17.698 --> 08:20.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:20.400 --> 08:24.705
It's so wonderful
to see you all so happy.

08:24.705 --> 08:26.707
[indistinct chatter]

08:26.707 --> 08:28.342
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:28.442 --> 08:32.746
Helene, I just love
seeing you at the bar.

08:32.746 --> 08:34.748
Oh, come on, do a little...

08:34.748 --> 08:37.818
Uh-huh.

08:37.818 --> 08:40.420
[chuckling] Oh.

08:42.256 --> 08:44.324
Thanks for the hookup,
granny friend.

08:44.324 --> 08:47.261
Mm-hmm.
Just remember our deal.

08:47.261 --> 08:49.763
Bottomless daiquiris--
got it.

08:49.763 --> 08:53.000
- Yes.
- [chuckles]

08:55.102 --> 08:56.937
[clears throat]

08:56.937 --> 08:59.006
You gonna open it?

09:00.674 --> 09:02.509
Just taking my time.

09:04.011 --> 09:07.214
Would you want to know?

09:07.214 --> 09:10.717
About a year ago, I was given
six months to live.

09:10.717 --> 09:14.121
That knowledge is what
brought me to this island,

09:14.121 --> 09:18.258
and this island
changed everything.

09:18.258 --> 09:21.228
But you're still alive.

09:21.228 --> 09:24.565
I'm a special case.

09:26.600 --> 09:30.103
So why do you...

09:30.103 --> 09:32.506
want to know
when you're gonna die?

09:34.007 --> 09:36.343
My dad...

09:36.343 --> 09:41.248
he, uh--he died of an aneurysm
when I was ten.

09:41.248 --> 09:43.984
I've always believed
that I'll die young, too.

09:46.386 --> 09:49.089
Quite the sword of Damocles
hanging over your head.

09:49.089 --> 09:51.491
Yeah, I've just come
to accept it--

09:51.491 --> 09:56.363
no long-term plans
or commitments.

09:56.363 --> 09:58.398
Oh. Wait a minute,
let me guess.

09:58.398 --> 10:01.101
You found someone
that you want to commit to.

10:01.101 --> 10:03.937
Oh, love changes everything.

10:03.937 --> 10:05.372
Yeah, not love.

10:05.372 --> 10:08.275
Yeah, I haven't even
asked her out yet, but, uh...

10:08.275 --> 10:11.044
Yeah, all of a sudden,
I have these urges

10:11.044 --> 10:14.414
to make plans for the future.

10:14.414 --> 10:17.217
It's not that I don't want
a family.

10:17.217 --> 10:19.219
I...

10:19.219 --> 10:21.822
I just don't want
to make anyone else

10:21.822 --> 10:24.024
feel that pain that I did.

10:25.659 --> 10:28.862
And if you open that envelope
and it says that you live

10:28.862 --> 10:31.098
until 99, then you'll--

10:31.098 --> 10:34.001
Then I-I'll ask her out.

10:35.269 --> 10:37.571
Hmm.

10:37.571 --> 10:41.508
You know, I always thought
knowledge was power,

10:41.508 --> 10:43.210
but...

10:43.210 --> 10:45.445
now I'm not so sure.

10:45.445 --> 10:48.248
What if I don't want to know?
[chuckles]

10:48.248 --> 10:49.349
Hmm.

10:49.349 --> 10:51.084
Well, that's probably why
it came in an envelope

10:51.084 --> 10:52.653
instead of sky writing.

10:52.653 --> 10:54.821
[chuckles]

10:54.922 --> 10:57.291
Yeah.
[chuckles]

10:57.291 --> 11:04.298
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:05.332 --> 11:07.634
Did any of you see
that great spotted ray?

11:07.634 --> 11:09.970
I was following a school
of blue tang.

11:09.970 --> 11:11.939
I think I got a sunburn
on my butt.

11:11.939 --> 11:13.207
[laughter]

11:13.307 --> 11:15.375
That was
a dream vacation day, guys.

11:15.375 --> 11:17.377
Thank you so much
for making the effort.

11:17.377 --> 11:19.112
Are you kidding?
Mom, that was awesome.

11:19.213 --> 11:21.081
Yeah, maybe it was
just the fresh air,

11:21.181 --> 11:23.584
but I feel
so damn happy right now.

11:23.584 --> 11:25.219
Me too.

11:25.319 --> 11:26.086
Wow.

11:26.086 --> 11:28.255
Okay, so what now?

11:28.255 --> 11:30.624
- Who wants lobster?
- Oh, me.

11:30.624 --> 11:32.392
Yeah, me too.

11:34.494 --> 11:36.964
Lobster it is.
[scattered chuckles]

11:36.964 --> 11:40.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:44.071 --> 11:47.374
[distant thudding]

11:56.283 --> 11:58.819
Dan?

11:58.819 --> 12:00.954
Do you hear that?

12:00.954 --> 12:02.923
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

12:02.923 --> 12:05.926
[thudding continues]

12:05.926 --> 12:13.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:24.845 --> 12:27.481
[grunts]

12:27.481 --> 12:30.851
[grunting]

12:30.851 --> 12:33.587
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:33.587 --> 12:34.888
Ryleigh?

12:34.888 --> 12:36.957
Honey.

12:36.957 --> 12:39.793
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:39.793 --> 12:41.061
Ry?

12:41.061 --> 12:42.930
Oh, hey, Mom.

12:42.930 --> 12:45.098
You want to get that volley in?

12:45.098 --> 12:47.134
Honey, it's late.
You should be in bed.

12:47.134 --> 12:49.236
Oh, I'm not tired.

12:49.236 --> 12:50.504
Come on.

12:50.504 --> 12:53.607
You can pick this up again
in the morning.

12:53.607 --> 12:54.741
Okay.

12:54.741 --> 13:01.982
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:07.421 --> 13:10.757
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

13:10.757 --> 13:14.428
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:14.528 --> 13:16.964
Hola, Javier.

13:16.964 --> 13:18.465
What's up, Ruby?

13:18.465 --> 13:20.801
Oh, nothing much.

13:20.801 --> 13:23.637
Just learning some Spanish.

13:23.637 --> 13:25.138
Um, not to be...

13:25.138 --> 13:27.741
[in Spanish]
The relationship police...

13:27.741 --> 13:30.177
[in English]
But...

13:30.177 --> 13:32.980
Elena seemed
pretty upset yesterday.

13:35.115 --> 13:37.317
You want to tell me
what you did?

13:38.185 --> 13:40.053
She said I did something?

13:40.053 --> 13:41.555
I mean, not exactly.

13:41.555 --> 13:44.157
I mean, she didn't
actually say anything.

13:44.157 --> 13:46.059
I-I just kind of assumed.

13:46.059 --> 13:47.995
You know, all I did

13:47.995 --> 13:50.097
was everything she asked,
all right?

13:50.097 --> 13:51.999
I-I kept our relationship
a secret

13:51.999 --> 13:53.433
when she wanted
to keep it a secret.

13:53.433 --> 13:56.136
I learned salsa
'cause she likes to dance.

13:56.136 --> 13:57.504
Threw her a prom.

13:57.504 --> 14:02.009
Ruby, I made her a chair
out of rattan.

14:02.009 --> 14:03.944
And do--do you have any idea
how long it takes

14:03.944 --> 14:06.647
to make a chair out of rattan?

14:06.647 --> 14:08.882
A lot of time.

14:08.882 --> 14:11.118
But I enjoyed doing it

14:11.118 --> 14:13.020
'cause I was doing it for her

14:13.020 --> 14:16.056
because
of what she meant to me.

14:16.056 --> 14:18.058
Past tense.

14:18.058 --> 14:19.593
You don't know?

14:20.994 --> 14:22.996
Elena broke up with me.

14:22.996 --> 14:24.998
What?

14:24.998 --> 14:28.635
- Why?
- She didn't say.

14:28.635 --> 14:29.837
No.

14:29.837 --> 14:31.371
That doesn't make any sense.

14:31.371 --> 14:34.842
Yep, that's exactly
how I felt.

14:34.842 --> 14:39.046
I am so sorry.
I-I had no idea.

14:39.046 --> 14:41.548
I appreciate you.

14:41.548 --> 14:43.183
I really do.

14:43.183 --> 14:47.120
And I don't know
what Elena needs, clearly...

14:47.120 --> 14:49.556
but I could use
some time alone.

14:51.825 --> 14:54.928
Um... yeah.

14:54.928 --> 14:56.597
Of course.

14:56.597 --> 15:03.570
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:12.779 --> 15:14.214
Ryleigh,
let me see that hand.

15:14.314 --> 15:17.451
It's fine, Mom, really.

15:19.119 --> 15:22.923
- This doesn't hurt?
- No, don't feel a thing.

15:22.923 --> 15:29.696
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:46.547 --> 15:48.048
Amber.

15:48.048 --> 15:49.850
How are you enjoying
your happy family?

15:49.850 --> 15:51.852
Oh, um...

15:51.852 --> 15:53.654
good, I guess.

15:53.654 --> 15:54.855
Great.

15:54.855 --> 15:57.291
Walk with me.

15:57.291 --> 15:59.760
Dan planned a date
for us tonight.

15:59.760 --> 16:01.261
I didn't even have to hint.

16:01.261 --> 16:04.598
Oh, sounds like he's
seeing you like that again.

16:04.598 --> 16:06.099
[chuckles]

16:06.099 --> 16:07.401
The boys are bonding.

16:07.401 --> 16:10.971
Ryleigh suddenly loves
tennis again.

16:10.971 --> 16:14.141
But I don't know.
Something feels off.

16:14.141 --> 16:17.377
Maybe you're not used
to seeing them so happy.

16:17.377 --> 16:20.180
Maybe, but...

16:20.180 --> 16:22.249
it doesn't feel real.

16:22.249 --> 16:24.351
Amber, you asked
for your family to be happy

16:24.351 --> 16:26.987
the way they are
on social media, correct?

16:26.987 --> 16:29.256
Well, it looks to me
like they are.

16:30.424 --> 16:32.926
You know what?
I'm not gonna second-guess.

16:32.926 --> 16:35.829
I'm just going to enjoy it.

16:35.829 --> 16:37.631
It's everything I ever wanted.

16:37.631 --> 16:41.134
So, if you'll excuse me, I have
to get ready for my date.

16:41.235 --> 16:43.937
I am sure it will be
an unforgettable night.

16:43.937 --> 16:46.106
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:46.106 --> 16:49.276
[indistinct chatter]

16:49.276 --> 16:52.513
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:52.513 --> 16:53.313
Hey.

16:53.313 --> 16:57.150
Envelope guy,
you're back.

16:57.150 --> 16:59.953
- Yeah.
- Can I get you anything?

16:59.953 --> 17:01.922
I'll get a beer.

17:01.922 --> 17:03.223
Sure.

17:03.223 --> 17:06.360
[indistinct chatter continues]

17:06.360 --> 17:08.562
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:08.662 --> 17:09.863
Thanks.

17:09.863 --> 17:13.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:13.166 --> 17:15.802
Okay, look, I know
you didn't ask me or anything,

17:15.802 --> 17:17.671
but I wouldn't want to know.

17:17.671 --> 17:22.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:22.042 --> 17:23.777
Hey, Dad-vier.

17:23.777 --> 17:26.847
Noncommittal, that tracks.
What are you doing back there?

17:26.847 --> 17:28.315
Oh, Ruby got me a job.

17:28.315 --> 17:31.051
Figured it was better than
sitting around all day, so...

17:31.051 --> 17:33.587
That's great.
Can I get a beer?

17:33.587 --> 17:35.722
Coming right up?

17:35.722 --> 17:38.258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:38.258 --> 17:41.228
So... what's up
with the day drinking?

17:41.228 --> 17:43.297
Elena broke up with me

17:43.297 --> 17:47.000
and is apparently leaving it
up to me to tell everyone.

17:47.000 --> 17:49.203
- Ouch.
- Yeah.

17:49.203 --> 17:51.538
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:51.538 --> 17:54.508
- No way.
- Sorry. I should have asked.

17:54.508 --> 17:56.543
No, you're fine.
I eat them, too, like, all day.

17:56.543 --> 17:59.780
I guess I must have inherited
that from you.

17:59.780 --> 18:01.815
[chuckles]

18:01.815 --> 18:07.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:07.321 --> 18:08.388
Hey, Mom.

18:08.388 --> 18:11.658
- Uh, do you need help with that?
- Sure.

18:18.232 --> 18:22.336
Mom! Mom, we're here!
Please, Mom, help us!

18:22.336 --> 18:25.405
We're here!
Please, Mom, help us!

18:25.405 --> 18:26.840
There.

18:26.840 --> 18:29.343
- There you go.
- [gasps]

18:33.881 --> 18:36.817
[soft elegant music playing]

18:36.817 --> 18:38.819
♪ ♪

18:38.819 --> 18:40.787
[bottle rattles in ice]

18:40.787 --> 18:44.958
♪ ♪

18:44.958 --> 18:46.960
This is amazing, Dan.

18:46.960 --> 18:49.630
Still less than you deserve.

18:49.630 --> 18:53.333
Is everything all right?
Would you prefer wine?

18:53.333 --> 18:55.102
I just...

18:55.102 --> 18:57.137
Does Ryleigh seem all right
to you?

18:57.137 --> 19:00.807
Tonight is about us, my love,
not the kids.

19:00.807 --> 19:02.042
I know.

19:02.042 --> 19:04.244
It's just I...

19:04.244 --> 19:07.548
I think I'm losing my mind
or something.

19:07.548 --> 19:11.351
Have I told you lately
how beautiful you are?

19:11.351 --> 19:14.721
No, not in a long time, actually.

19:14.721 --> 19:15.956
Then let me do it now.

19:15.956 --> 19:18.825
You are so beautiful

19:18.825 --> 19:21.195
inside and out.

19:21.195 --> 19:23.931
Do you really feel that way?

19:23.931 --> 19:26.033
You're my wife.

19:26.133 --> 19:28.602
I love you.

19:28.602 --> 19:30.604
Yeah.

19:30.604 --> 19:34.708
If something's wrong,
I'm always here for you.

19:37.544 --> 19:40.047
When I was getting ready
for dinner, Ryleigh came in,

19:40.047 --> 19:42.115
and when she was
in front of the mirror,

19:42.115 --> 19:45.118
it was like her reflection
was different...

19:45.118 --> 19:47.087
like there was another Ryleigh
behind the mirror

19:47.087 --> 19:48.856
and she was trapped
and terrified

19:48.856 --> 19:50.257
and calling out to me.

19:50.257 --> 19:52.726
That must have been frightening,

19:52.726 --> 19:54.461
but the kids are fine.

19:54.461 --> 19:56.830
Let's just be present
with each other.

19:56.830 --> 19:58.332
- Dan--
- I feel like

19:58.332 --> 20:00.300
I'm really seeing you
for the first time in forever.

20:00.300 --> 20:03.103
Really? Because I feel
like you're not hearing me.

20:03.103 --> 20:05.472
I feel like you're not here.

20:05.472 --> 20:08.642
I was saving this
for after dinner, but...

20:08.642 --> 20:10.210
I just can't wait.

20:11.445 --> 20:12.613
Oh, my God.

20:12.613 --> 20:16.650
A tennis mom
should have a tennis bracelet.

20:21.221 --> 20:23.590
I don't know what to say.

20:23.590 --> 20:25.826
♪ ♪

20:25.826 --> 20:27.995
[chuckles]

20:27.995 --> 20:29.897
Say you'll dance with me.

20:29.897 --> 20:37.004
♪ ♪

20:55.122 --> 20:56.723
This is nice.

20:56.723 --> 21:00.127
♪ ♪

21:00.127 --> 21:03.030
- [knocking]
- Amber, can you hear me?

21:03.030 --> 21:05.065
Amber, I'm--I don't--

21:05.065 --> 21:07.701
Amber!
Hey, sweetheart, please!

21:07.701 --> 21:10.003
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

21:10.003 --> 21:11.939
Who are you?

21:11.939 --> 21:14.641
I'm the husband
you always wanted

21:14.641 --> 21:16.944
No.

21:16.944 --> 21:19.813
Amber, don't go.

21:19.813 --> 21:23.417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:24.751 --> 21:25.953
Hello.

21:25.953 --> 21:27.921
Ruby, I am buried
in work here.

21:27.921 --> 21:29.656
So, please...

21:29.656 --> 21:31.992
I spoke with Javier,

21:31.992 --> 21:34.228
and he said
that you broke things off

21:34.228 --> 21:36.263
without explanation.

21:36.263 --> 21:39.900
Elena, why would you do that?

21:39.900 --> 21:42.102
I think I made a mistake.

21:42.102 --> 21:44.204
You know,
I think you did, too,

21:44.204 --> 21:45.973
because that man loves you.

21:45.973 --> 21:48.008
Ruby, not with Javier, okay?

21:48.008 --> 21:49.443
With you.

21:49.443 --> 21:51.945
- With me?
- Yes.

21:51.945 --> 21:54.381
I think I've let us
get too close,

21:54.381 --> 21:57.818
and boundaries
have gotten blurry.

21:57.818 --> 22:00.888
[scoffs] Is that right?

22:00.888 --> 22:02.589
I think it's probably best

22:02.589 --> 22:06.793
if we keep this relationship
more professional.

22:06.793 --> 22:08.262
Hmm?

22:08.262 --> 22:10.497
Well, because I'm your friend

22:10.497 --> 22:12.599
and I can see
that you're in pain,

22:12.599 --> 22:16.403
I'm gonna go ahead and step
back and give you your space.

22:16.403 --> 22:20.174
But like I used
to tell my kids,

22:20.174 --> 22:22.409
just because you're hurting

22:22.409 --> 22:26.513
doesn't mean you get to go
around hurting other people.

22:28.015 --> 22:30.050
Good night, Elena.

22:30.050 --> 22:33.220
<i>[soft music]</i>

22:33.220 --> 22:35.489
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:35.489 --> 22:37.824
Ruby.

22:37.824 --> 22:39.626
Hey!

22:39.626 --> 22:42.296
What did you do to my family?

22:42.296 --> 22:44.898
You asked for your family
to be happy.

22:44.898 --> 22:47.234
Aren't they?

22:47.234 --> 22:50.170
I don't know. Sort of.
I mean...

22:50.170 --> 22:52.472
they seem like they are, but
they're not themselves.

22:52.472 --> 22:55.709
Well, your fantasy wasn't for
your family to be themselves.

22:55.709 --> 22:57.211
Of course it was.

22:57.211 --> 22:58.345
It was for them to be happy

22:58.345 --> 23:00.247
being the people
you want them to be,

23:00.247 --> 23:02.850
the people you present them
as on social media.

23:02.850 --> 23:08.021
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:08.021 --> 23:11.491
A picture is--
is only the surface.

23:11.491 --> 23:14.394
But... I don't want them
to be surface happy.

23:14.394 --> 23:18.131
I want them to feel it
on the inside.

23:18.232 --> 23:20.100
Then why
don't you stop focusing

23:20.200 --> 23:22.936
on Dan and Ryleigh
and Trevor

23:22.936 --> 23:26.940
and you start
focusing on Amber?

23:26.940 --> 23:28.909
What makes you happy?

23:28.909 --> 23:30.811
And not on the surface--

23:30.811 --> 23:34.648
I mean truly, deeply happy.

23:34.648 --> 23:36.984
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:36.984 --> 23:38.352
I mean...

23:38.352 --> 23:40.954
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:40.954 --> 23:43.957
My family does.

23:43.957 --> 23:46.827
That was quite a pause.

23:46.827 --> 23:48.996
Look inside yourself, Amber.

23:48.996 --> 23:51.899
Like, really, really look...

23:51.899 --> 23:54.735
at who you are,
at what you want.

23:54.735 --> 23:56.503
See those answers?

23:56.503 --> 23:59.273
They're gonna bring you closer
to your family.

23:59.273 --> 24:04.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:04.211 --> 24:07.381
[distant clattering]

24:07.381 --> 24:14.521
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:19.560 --> 24:20.861
Trevor?

24:20.861 --> 24:22.229
Oh, hey, Mom.

24:22.229 --> 24:25.566
- What did you do?
- I smashed it all.

24:25.566 --> 24:26.834
But why?

24:26.834 --> 24:30.003
I don't need all this stuff.
Computers can't love you back.

24:30.003 --> 24:31.872
You know, only family
can do that.

24:31.872 --> 24:37.711
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:37.711 --> 24:39.146
Mom, please!

24:39.246 --> 24:42.816
I'm scared!
I don't know what to do!

24:42.816 --> 24:45.819
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

24:45.819 --> 24:49.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:49.323 --> 24:52.492
There you are.
I was worried about you, babe.

24:52.492 --> 24:53.827
No.

24:53.927 --> 24:56.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:56.396 --> 24:59.600
[breathes deeply]

24:59.600 --> 25:01.835
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:01.835 --> 25:04.037
Look at myself.

25:04.037 --> 25:06.640
Really look.

25:06.640 --> 25:09.776
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:09.776 --> 25:12.312
I am a mess.

25:12.312 --> 25:19.520
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:23.824 --> 25:25.826
[gasps]

25:25.826 --> 25:31.999
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:35.435 --> 25:38.338
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:38.338 --> 25:45.479
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:08.569 --> 26:10.537
[sighs]

26:19.713 --> 26:21.849
One times one is one.

26:21.849 --> 26:25.052
One times two is two.

26:26.220 --> 26:29.256
One times three is three.

26:29.256 --> 26:31.992
Always know where the exit is.

26:36.496 --> 26:39.266
One times four is four.

26:41.001 --> 26:43.403
One times five is five.

26:44.938 --> 26:47.975
One times six is six.

26:49.276 --> 26:52.679
One times seven is seven.

26:52.679 --> 26:55.749
One times eight is eight.

26:55.749 --> 26:58.919
<i>[haunting music]</i>

26:58.919 --> 27:00.254
Hello?

27:00.254 --> 27:02.122
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:02.122 --> 27:05.926
Is anybody--anybody there?

27:05.926 --> 27:07.961
[sighs]

27:07.961 --> 27:10.964
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:10.964 --> 27:13.934
[creature snarling]

27:13.934 --> 27:18.772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:18.772 --> 27:20.908
[whimpers]

27:20.908 --> 27:22.876
[shouts]

27:22.876 --> 27:25.846
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

27:25.846 --> 27:32.853
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:32.953 --> 27:35.989
[thudding]

27:35.989 --> 27:42.663
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:42.663 --> 27:45.232
[breathes deeply]

27:45.232 --> 27:47.968
Two times one is two.

27:47.968 --> 27:50.838
Two times three is six.

27:50.838 --> 27:53.841
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:53.841 --> 27:56.210
2 times 6 is 12.

27:56.210 --> 28:03.383
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:08.655 --> 28:11.258
2 times 7 is 14.

28:11.258 --> 28:17.664
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:17.664 --> 28:19.867
2 times 8 is 16.

28:19.867 --> 28:23.871
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:23.871 --> 28:26.673
2 times 10 is 20.

28:26.673 --> 28:30.711
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:30.711 --> 28:34.014
2 times 11 is 22.

28:34.014 --> 28:36.917
[distant thud]

28:36.917 --> 28:40.687
2 times 12 is 24.

28:40.687 --> 28:47.661
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:02.876 --> 29:05.846
<i>[soft eerie music]</i>

29:05.846 --> 29:13.020
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:30.237 --> 29:32.639
Look inside yourself.

29:34.408 --> 29:36.510
Honey, it's us.

29:37.978 --> 29:39.513
Oh, thank God!

29:41.481 --> 29:44.284
[door rattling,
creature screams]

29:44.284 --> 29:47.187
How in the world
did you find us?

29:47.187 --> 29:50.224
Luck, but maybe
mother's love led me to you.

29:50.224 --> 29:51.491
You did not just say that.

29:51.491 --> 29:53.527
Just let her be mushy
for once.

29:53.527 --> 29:56.029
I keep finding things
from my childhood

29:56.029 --> 29:58.031
in this...

29:58.031 --> 30:00.234
awful place.

30:00.234 --> 30:01.401
If you remember them,

30:01.401 --> 30:03.370
they must have been
important to you.

30:03.370 --> 30:06.807
Yeah, Mom, you never really
talk about when you were a kid.

30:06.807 --> 30:09.776
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:09.776 --> 30:12.246
Because it was not great.

30:12.246 --> 30:14.047
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:14.047 --> 30:16.250
It was terrible.

30:16.250 --> 30:18.318
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:18.318 --> 30:21.522
I basically lived
out of this backpack.

30:22.856 --> 30:25.325
And this racket...

30:25.325 --> 30:27.694
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:27.694 --> 30:29.696
I found it in a dumpster.

30:29.696 --> 30:31.398
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:31.398 --> 30:33.400
I begged my parents
for tennis lessons.

30:33.400 --> 30:37.137
I wanted so badly to be
on a team, to belong somewhere.

30:37.237 --> 30:40.841
That's why you want me
to play so bad.

30:40.841 --> 30:43.877
I want you to have everything
I didn't have,

30:43.877 --> 30:46.079
both of you.

30:46.079 --> 30:48.115
And I'm trying so hard
to give it to you,

30:48.115 --> 30:50.817
and I'm getting it all wrong.

30:50.817 --> 30:53.487
You're not alone in that.

30:53.487 --> 30:57.124
I'm so sorry I brought us
to this island.

30:57.124 --> 30:58.358
We're all sorry about stuff,

30:58.358 --> 31:01.862
but we also got to get
out of here.

31:01.862 --> 31:04.198
It's quiet now.

31:04.198 --> 31:07.100
Maybe whatever was out there
has moved on.

31:07.100 --> 31:10.838
[exhales deeply]

31:10.838 --> 31:12.739
I think I know a way out.

31:12.739 --> 31:15.709
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

31:15.709 --> 31:20.214
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:20.214 --> 31:23.984
[all shout, wind gusting]

31:23.984 --> 31:26.253
- Aah!
- Aah!

31:26.253 --> 31:28.255
- It's back.
- What do we do?

31:28.255 --> 31:32.025
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:32.025 --> 31:34.127
- Go, go, go, go, go!
- Go, go, go, go!

31:34.127 --> 31:36.296
[Amber shouts indistinctly]

31:36.296 --> 31:42.469
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:42.469 --> 31:43.937
That way!

31:43.937 --> 31:50.744
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:55.849 --> 31:57.851
- Aah!
- Dan!

31:57.851 --> 32:00.954
- Are you okay?
- Keep going!

32:00.954 --> 32:03.123
Kids, go, down the hall!

32:03.123 --> 32:04.958
Look for the room with the X.

32:04.958 --> 32:07.127
- Go!
- Ah! I think it's twisted.

32:07.127 --> 32:09.663
Oh! Go, go, go!

32:11.398 --> 32:14.034
- Come on! Hurry up!
- Come on, guys!

32:14.034 --> 32:16.670
- Come on, hurry up!
- Run!

32:16.670 --> 32:18.238
Run, faster!

32:18.238 --> 32:21.208
Come on!

32:21.208 --> 32:22.843
- You're almost there!
- It's waiting!

32:22.843 --> 32:23.844
both: Come on!

32:23.844 --> 32:30.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:30.083 --> 32:31.919
We need to barricade it.

32:31.919 --> 32:33.720
I'll be right back.

32:33.720 --> 32:35.289
- Quick, grab an end.
- [grunts]

32:35.289 --> 32:37.157
It's heavy.
Oh. Oh. We got it. Go. Go.

32:37.257 --> 32:39.660
Hurry, Mom.
We need help, please.

32:39.660 --> 32:41.094
Hurry, Amber.

32:41.195 --> 32:43.363
Roarke, I found them.

32:43.363 --> 32:44.331
Get us out here.

32:44.331 --> 32:46.366
- I can't.
- Why the hell not?

32:46.366 --> 32:49.169
Amber,
you still don't understand.

32:49.169 --> 32:52.673
The only person who can save
your family is you.

32:52.673 --> 32:54.641
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:58.011 --> 33:00.948
[jazz music playing]

33:00.948 --> 33:04.218
♪ ♪

33:04.218 --> 33:06.553
- What's this?
- Zombie.

33:06.553 --> 33:10.791
Brandy, rum, pineapple juice,
and a splash of lime.

33:10.791 --> 33:11.992
I didn't order a Zombie.

33:11.992 --> 33:14.094
Yeah, well,
it seemed appropriate.

33:14.094 --> 33:15.929
Okay, I'll bite.

33:15.929 --> 33:17.664
Uh, appropriate because?

33:17.664 --> 33:21.502
Because you're living
like you're dead, obviously.

33:21.502 --> 33:23.170
I mean, look, that girl
that you like

33:23.170 --> 33:25.706
is probably out there
somewhere finding someone.

33:25.706 --> 33:26.640
And what are you doing?

33:26.773 --> 33:29.209
You're staring at an envelope
for two days.

33:29.209 --> 33:31.245
I don't recall asking
for your hot take.

33:31.245 --> 33:32.412
Well, I'm a bartender,

33:32.412 --> 33:34.915
so it kind of comes
with the territory.

33:34.915 --> 33:36.316
[scoffs]

33:36.316 --> 33:39.286
Dude, you're
in a tropical paradise.

33:39.286 --> 33:42.456
♪ ♪

33:42.456 --> 33:43.423
Let's go.

33:43.524 --> 33:45.826
Go where?
Don't you have customers?

33:45.826 --> 33:48.462
It's free.
They can serve themselves.

33:48.462 --> 33:49.296
Come on.

33:49.296 --> 33:51.765
♪ ♪

33:59.573 --> 34:00.707
Shoes off.

34:00.707 --> 34:04.778
I bet you haven't even put
your feet in the water yet.

34:04.778 --> 34:06.813
[sighs]

34:06.813 --> 34:09.216
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

34:09.216 --> 34:11.451
There. Are you happy?

34:11.451 --> 34:14.188
- Ooh!
- [laughing] I'm getting there.

34:14.188 --> 34:17.224
There, is that enough?

34:17.224 --> 34:20.194
[laughs, squeals]

34:20.194 --> 34:22.095
Amber, this is your fantasy.

34:22.095 --> 34:24.765
Everything that happens here
comes from you.

34:24.765 --> 34:26.066
Only you can let it go.

34:26.066 --> 34:29.203
Let what go?
What does that mean?

34:29.203 --> 34:32.005
Talk to your family.
They can help.

34:32.005 --> 34:34.942
What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

34:34.942 --> 34:37.477
Come back here, you bitch.

34:37.477 --> 34:39.146
[groans]

34:39.246 --> 34:42.349
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

34:42.349 --> 34:48.555
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:56.396 --> 35:00.334
My mom was 39 when she died.

35:01.869 --> 35:04.004
You're not the only one.

35:06.974 --> 35:09.343
At her funeral, there were...

35:09.443 --> 35:11.411
people that
I had never met before

35:11.411 --> 35:14.915
who were devastated and sobbing
that they had lost her.

35:14.915 --> 35:17.384
<i>[soft music]</i>

35:17.384 --> 35:19.720
I still get letters from people

35:19.720 --> 35:22.689
who just want to tell me how
important she was to them...

35:22.689 --> 35:24.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:24.458 --> 35:28.962
How crushed and how they
still pick up the phone

35:28.962 --> 35:31.698
to call her and then remember--

35:31.698 --> 35:35.035
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:35.035 --> 35:37.204
I'm sorry.

35:37.204 --> 35:40.941
[sighs]
You're missing the point.

35:40.941 --> 35:43.944
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:43.944 --> 35:47.314
My mom did things right.

35:47.314 --> 35:51.251
You're supposed to leave people
devastated when you go.

35:52.653 --> 35:55.689
The more tears,
the better you lived your life.

35:55.689 --> 35:58.091
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:58.091 --> 35:59.826
I mean, if people don't care
when you go,

35:59.826 --> 36:02.429
then, God, what's the point?

36:04.498 --> 36:09.203
I don't know
what's in your envelope, but...

36:09.203 --> 36:10.904
it shouldn't matter.

36:10.904 --> 36:12.973
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:12.973 --> 36:16.643
One thing I do know is that...

36:16.643 --> 36:19.847
my mom would not have changed
a single thing.

36:19.847 --> 36:21.582
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:21.582 --> 36:25.552
[sniffles] And I bet your dad
wouldn't have either.

36:25.552 --> 36:29.022
[chuckles]

36:29.022 --> 36:31.358
[exhales sharply]

36:31.358 --> 36:38.565
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:41.568 --> 36:43.203
Here.

36:43.203 --> 36:46.807
You want me to open it?

36:46.807 --> 36:48.909
No.

36:48.909 --> 36:52.279
I want you to burn it.

36:52.279 --> 36:58.352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:58.352 --> 37:00.888
- Keep holding.
- Oh, it's too strong.

37:00.888 --> 37:02.689
- Did you find a way out?
- No.

37:02.689 --> 37:07.160
- Mom, I'm scared.
- I've got you. I always have.

37:07.160 --> 37:10.230
- I know it didn't feel like it.
- But it did, Mom.

37:10.230 --> 37:12.266
All that stuff that you
wanted to give us,

37:12.366 --> 37:14.935
everything that
you didn't have, we have it.

37:14.935 --> 37:16.904
We love you just
the way you are.

37:16.904 --> 37:18.138
You are enough.

37:18.238 --> 37:20.807
It's just--sometimes
it feels like we're not.

37:20.807 --> 37:22.142
Oh, but you are.

37:22.142 --> 37:25.379
You're perfect
just the way you are.

37:25.379 --> 37:26.480
And, Ryleigh,

37:26.480 --> 37:29.383
I don't care if you play tennis
or drive race cars

37:29.383 --> 37:32.352
or knit sweaters--
you are spectacular.

37:32.352 --> 37:34.888
And I'm sorry
I didn't say it every day.

37:34.888 --> 37:37.057
And, Trev, honey,
I just miss you,

37:37.057 --> 37:39.126
but that's on me.

37:39.126 --> 37:41.128
You are doing your best
to make your way

37:41.128 --> 37:42.596
through a difficult time
in your life,

37:42.596 --> 37:45.299
and I need to love you enough
to give you space.

37:45.299 --> 37:47.367
Mom, I-I think
it's slowing down.

37:47.467 --> 37:49.236
Keep--keep talking.
Amber, keep talking.

37:49.236 --> 37:51.171
Whatever this is,
it's connected to you.

37:51.171 --> 37:53.507
Dan, I love you so much.

37:53.507 --> 37:56.910
I'm sorry I couldn't see what
a wonderful life we'd built.

37:56.910 --> 37:59.246
I see it now.

38:01.715 --> 38:02.883
I do.

38:02.883 --> 38:04.985
I see you.

38:09.923 --> 38:11.124
We're okay.

38:11.124 --> 38:12.726
- You did it.
- We did it.

38:12.726 --> 38:14.761
Ryleigh,
say something sarcastic

38:14.761 --> 38:16.129
so I know it's really you.

38:16.129 --> 38:18.565
Where are we going
on vacation next year--

38:18.565 --> 38:22.035
North Korea?
[laughter]

38:23.971 --> 38:25.439
[sighs]

38:31.078 --> 38:32.679
You're up early.

38:32.679 --> 38:34.414
- I haven't slept yet.
- Ah...

38:34.414 --> 38:37.551
The tireless work
of a bartender.

38:37.551 --> 38:39.086
What's up?

38:39.086 --> 38:42.456
[sighs]
Just checking on you.

38:42.456 --> 38:44.258
Everything's good.

38:44.258 --> 38:47.261
Uh, don't do that.
I do that.

38:47.261 --> 38:48.362
Do what?

38:48.362 --> 38:50.664
Shut down,
pretend like everything's fine,

38:50.664 --> 38:52.633
refuse help.

38:54.601 --> 38:57.471
Look, I know neither of us
is gonna like it,

38:57.471 --> 39:01.375
but we have a real opportunity
to dig deeper here.

39:02.976 --> 39:05.145
And I think we should take it.

39:05.145 --> 39:08.215
[<i>Brianna Lea Pruett's
"Under Your Wing"</i>]

39:08.215 --> 39:09.550
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:09.650 --> 39:11.852
How do you take your coffee?

39:11.852 --> 39:14.221
Oat milk, three stevias.

39:15.789 --> 39:18.225
We'll work on that.

39:18.225 --> 39:25.399
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:40.247 --> 39:43.350
<i>♪ Oh, your love for me ♪</i>

39:43.350 --> 39:47.087
<i>♪ Is no dangerous sea ♪</i>

39:47.087 --> 39:49.957
<i>♪ It's a glorious thing ♪</i>

39:49.957 --> 39:52.893
<i>♪ Taken under your wing ♪</i>

39:52.893 --> 39:56.096
<i>♪ Oh, you shiver and shout ♪</i>

39:56.096 --> 39:59.266
<i>♪ With your spirit, but how ♪</i>

39:59.266 --> 40:01.935
<i>♪ That soft voice
speaks to me ♪</i>

40:01.935 --> 40:03.804
<i>♪ Taken under... ♪</i>

40:03.804 --> 40:06.173
Morning. Sleep well?

40:06.173 --> 40:07.474
Well, as your coworker,

40:07.474 --> 40:10.377
I don't think I'm required
to answer that.

40:10.377 --> 40:12.246
Good morning.

40:12.246 --> 40:14.348
Graham family, I am so happy

40:14.348 --> 40:16.984
to see you all smiling
and unscathed.

40:16.984 --> 40:19.353
- [laughter]
- Out of curiosity,

40:19.353 --> 40:21.989
are all the fantasies
you do here

40:21.989 --> 40:25.092
quite so existentially
threatening?

40:25.092 --> 40:27.828
- Mine was.
- [chuckles]

40:27.828 --> 40:31.198
Safe travels, Mr. Hughes.

40:31.198 --> 40:32.699
Bye.

40:32.699 --> 40:36.770
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:36.770 --> 40:37.638
Oh, you know what?

40:37.771 --> 40:39.373
We should take
a dumb family photo for Mom.

40:39.373 --> 40:40.407
- Yes. Yes, yes, I'll do it.
- Yeah.

40:40.407 --> 40:42.910
Uh, maybe Ruby could take
this one instead.

40:42.910 --> 40:44.878
- Actually--
- Sure. Okay.

40:44.878 --> 40:46.947
- It's probably safer.
- Yeah.

40:46.947 --> 40:49.116
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:49.116 --> 40:52.953
Thank you for everything.

40:52.953 --> 40:55.289
And I'm sorry
I called you the B word.

40:55.289 --> 40:58.959
You know, there have been
times that I deserve the label.

40:58.959 --> 41:01.295
[both giggle]

41:02.963 --> 41:06.266
<i>♪ Oh, the sweetness
of the time ♪</i>

41:06.266 --> 41:08.802
<i>♪ I spent waiting
like a bird ♪</i>

41:08.802 --> 41:10.938
Okay, come on in, come on in.

41:10.938 --> 41:13.040
All right,
everybody say "cheese."

41:13.040 --> 41:15.843
One, two, three, cheese!

41:15.843 --> 41:17.845
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:17.845 --> 41:20.714
[laughter]

41:22.449 --> 41:25.385
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

41:25.385 --> 41:28.255
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:28.255 --> 41:30.691
- [in Spanish]
- I'm sorry, Ruby.

41:30.691 --> 41:33.293
It's all right.

41:33.293 --> 41:35.262
[in English]
I know you had your reasons.

41:35.262 --> 41:38.232
And when you're ready,
you'll tell me.

41:38.232 --> 41:41.768
I will. When I'm ready.

41:41.768 --> 41:43.971
Yes, of course.

41:43.971 --> 41:46.240
- [gasps]
- Are you okay?

41:46.240 --> 41:49.843
Yeah, I thought I felt
my tattoo tingling.

41:49.843 --> 41:51.245
Um, it's fine.

41:51.345 --> 41:54.047
It's probably just a chill
or something.

41:54.047 --> 41:56.183
[chuckles] I'm all right.

41:56.183 --> 41:59.353
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

41:59.453 --> 42:06.560
<i>♪ ♪</i>
